data.name: DeviceRegistrationExplanation.Text
data.value: You need to register each client device ID that synchronises with the activiser™ Database. This device ID can be found on the client during the initial setup or on the 'About' screen.

data.name: RegistrationExplanation.Text
data.value: Please enter your License details as supplied by activiser™ Limited

data.name: MailServerExplanation.Text
data.value:
To send various alerts, and job notifications to client, the activiser™ web service needs access to an SMTP server.
Please provide either the DNS domain name or IP address of your SMTP Server, and the port number (SMTP default port is 25)
Additionally, please provide the 'activiser' and 'administrator' mail addresses; The 'activiser' mail address is the 'From' address for email sent by the activiser web service. The 'administrator' mail address is the email address of the person responsible for administering activiser.
To test the server, click the 'Test' button, and an email will be sent to the 'administrator' email address.

data.name: SmsMessageExplanation.Text
data.value:
Enter the mobile alert message below. Note that the size of each message is limited to 160 characters. If exceeded, the message will be truncated.
The <Request> tag is used to represent the request number and the <Client> tag is used to represent the client name.

data.name: MobileAlertInstructions.Text
data.value: Mobile alerts are sent through an SMS Provider via email. Please enter the SMS provider email address template in the field below. The sequence '<Number>' represents the mobile phone number in the address. e.g.: <Number>@SMSProvider.com
